{
  "version": 2,
  "routes": [
    { "src": "/api/chat", "dest": "/api/index.js" }
  ]

  
"_comment": "version": 2 → Specifies that you're using Vercel's latest routing system.
"_comment": "routes" → Defines custom API routing behavior.
"_comment": "src": "/api/chat" → When a request is made to /api/chat on your Vercel app, it should trigger the backend.
"_comment": "dest": "/api/index.js" → This tells Vercel to forward the request to index.js inside the /api folder, where your backend logic is written.



  
}
